ngram\": \"your device\", \"from\": 1152, \"to\": 1163}, {\"ngram\": \"data\", \"from\": 1176, \"to\": 1180}, {\"ngram\": \"your activity\", \"from\": 1187, \"to\": 1200}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Please review their details and accept them to load the content.Manage Preferences From RT\\u00c9 Archives, profile of marathon runner, Olympia and bus conductor Bertie Messitt During his career, he held16 national recordsin distances ranging from 3,000m to the marathon.\", \"from\": 1202, \"to\": 1469, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1291, \"end\": 1294, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\", \"score\": 0.9835396432123026, \"rank\": 0.013767790549921992, \"text\": \"RT\\u00c9\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\"}, {\"begin\": 1333, \"end\": 1340, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia_London\", \"score\": 0.999999999953161, \"rank\": 4.695697953605618e-11, \"text\": \"Olympia\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia_London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia_London\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"their details\", \"from\": 1216, \"to\": 1229}, {\"ngram\": \"the content\", \"from\": 1254, \"to\": 1265}, {\"ngram\": \"Preferences\", \"from\": 1273, \"to\": 1284}, {\"ngram\": \"profile\", \"from\": 1304, \"to\": 1311}, {\"ngram\": \"marathon runner\", \"from\": 1315, \"to\": 1330}, {\"ngram\": \"bus conductor\", \"from\": 1344, \"to\": 1357}, {\"ngram\": \"his career\", \"from\": 1380, \"to\": 1390}, {\"ngram\": \"national recordsin distances\", \"from\": 1402, \"to\": 1430}, {\"ngram\": \"3,000m\", \"from\": 1444, \"to\": 1450}, {\"ngram\": \"the marathon\", \"from\": 1454, \"to\": 1466}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He was selected by the Olympic Council to represent Ireland in the marathon at the1960 Olympics in Romealongside his teammatesWillie Dunneand George McIntyre.\", \"from\": 1470, \"to\": 1628, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1522, \"end\": 1529, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.8784462415710486e-14, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Council\", \"from\": 1489, \"to\": 1508}, {\"ngram\": \"the marathon\", \"from\": 1533, \"to\": 1545}, {\"ngram\": \"the1960 Olympics\", \"from\": 1549, \"to\": 1565}, {\"ngram\": \"Romealongside\", \"from\": 1569, \"to\": 1582}, {\"ngram\": \"his teammatesWillie\", \"from\": 1583, \"to\": 1602}, {\"ngram\": \"Dunneand George McIntyre\", \"from\": 1603, \"to\": 1627}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lean, fresh faced and wearing a green vest with the number 58, Messitt was the frontrunner in the early stages of the race, which was famouslywonbyAbebe Bikila, who ran the marathon barefoot and won Ethiopia's first Olympic gold medal.\", \"from\": 1629, \"to\": 1864, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1828, \"end\": 1836, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"score\": 0.9998798954078891, \"rank\": 0.00011990570829033601, \"text\": \"Ethiopia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a green vest\", \"from\": 1659, \"to\": 1671}, {\"ngram\": \"the number\", \"from\": 1677, \"to\": 1687}, {\"ngram\": \"Messitt\", \"from\": 1692, \"to\": 1699}, {\"ngram\": \"the frontrunner\", \"from\": 1704, \"to\": 1719}, {\"ngram\": \"the early stages\", \"from\": 1723, \"to\": 1739}, {\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 1743, \"to\": 1751}, {\"ngram\": \"famouslywonbyAbebe Bikila\", \"from\": 1763, \"to\": 1788}, {\"ngram\": \"the marathon\", \"from\": 1798, \"to\": 1810}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Messitt unfortunately failed to finish the gruelling race.\", \"from\": 1865, \"to\": 1923, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Messitt\", \"from\": 1865, \"to\": 1872}, {\"ngram\": \"the gruelling race\", \"from\": 1904, \"to\": 1922}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Messitt competed in the European Athletics Championships in 1958 and was flag bearer for Ireland at the Championships in Belgrade in 1962, where he finished 13th out of a field of 28 athletes in the marathon.\", \"from\": 1925, \"to\": 2133, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2014, \"end\": 2021, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.8784462415710486e-14, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}, {\"begin\": 2046, \"end\": 2054, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgrade\", \"score\": 0.9999999996448423, \"rank\": 3.53681971037836e-10, \"text\": \"Belgrade\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgrade\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgrade\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Messitt\", \"from\": 1925, \"to\": 1932}, {\"ngram\": \"the European Athletics Championships\", \"from\": 1945, \"to\": 1981}, {\"ngram\": \"flag bearer\", \"from\": 1998, \"to\": 2009}, {\"ngram\": \"the Championships\", \"from\": 2025, \"to\": 2042}, {\"ngram\": \"a field\", \"from\": 2094, \"to\": 2101}, {\"ngram\": \"28 athletes\", \"from\": 2105, \"to\": 2116}, {\"ngram\": \"the marathon\", \"from\": 2120, \"to\": 2132}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He was a member ofDonore Harriers Athletics Cluband remained active in athletics long after his international career ended.\", \"from\": 2134, \"to\": 2257, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a member ofDonore Harriers Athletics Cluband\", \"from\": 2141, \"to\": 2185}, {\"ngram\": \"athletics\", \"from\": 2205, \"to\": 2214}, {\"ngram\": \"his international career\", \"from\": 2226, \"to\": 2250}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He formed an athletic club at the Dublin Bus garage in Donnybrook in the 1970s and was a founder of theBusiness Houses Athletic Association(BHAA), the body who launched the Dublin marathon.\", \"from\": 2258, \"to\": 2447, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2313, \"end\": 2323, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donnybrook_Stadium\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.255911551052116e-15, \"text\": \"Donnybrook\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donnybrook_Stadium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donnybrook_Stadium\"}, {\"begin\": 2431, \"end\": 2446, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dublin_Marathon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dublin marathon\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dublin_Marathon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dublin_Marathon\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an athletic club\", \"from\": 2268, \"to\": 2284}, {\"ngram\": \"the Dublin Bus garage\", \"from\": 2288, \"to\": 2309}, {\"ngram\": \"the 1970s\", \"from\": 2327, \"to\": 2336}, {\"ngram\": \"a founder\", \"from\": 2345, \"to\": 2354}, {\"ngram\": \"theBusiness Houses Athletic Association(BHAA\", \"from\": 2358, \"to\": 2402}, {\"ngram\": \"the body\", \"from\": 2405, \"to\": 2413}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Inspired by theNew York City Marathon, which had started in 1970, athleteNoel Carrolland RT\\u00c9 producer Louis HoganbelievedDublin could also host a marathon that would showcase the very best of the capital.\", \"from\": 2449, \"to\": 2653, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2538, \"end\": 2541, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\", \"score\": 0.9835396432123026, \"rank\": 0.013767790549921992, \"text\": \"RT\\u00c9\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"theNew York City Marathon\", \"from\": 2461, \"to\": 2486}, {\"ngram\": \"a marathon\", \"from\": 2593, \"to\": 2603}, {\"ngram\": \"the capital\", \"from\": 2641, \"to\": 2652}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Together with the BHAA and key figures in Dublin's civic and media sectors, they declared that the event would be \\\"one of the most efficiently organised marathons in Europe\\\".\", \"from\": 2654, \"to\": 2828, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2696, \"end\": 2702, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dublin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.481793470122267e-17, \"text\": \"Dublin\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dublin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dublin\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the BHAA\", \"from\": 2668, \"to\": 2676}, {\"ngram\": \"key figures\", \"from\": 2681, \"to\": 2692}, {\"ngram\": \"the event\", \"from\": 2749, \"to\": 2758}, {\"ngram\": \"the most efficiently organised marathons\", \"from\": 2776, \"to\": 2816}, {\"ngram\": \"Europe\", \"from\": 2820, \"to\": 2826}]}, {\"sentence\": \"TheEvening Pressnewspaper stated at the time that \\\"every detail from entry to the number of cups needed at drinking stations to the intricacies of timing have been thoroughly considered by a special committee\\\".\", \"from\": 2830, \"to\": 3040, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"TheEvening Pressnewspaper\", \"from\": 2830, \"to\": 2855}, {\"ngram\": \"the time\", \"from\": 2866, \"to\": 2874}, {\"ngram\": \"every detail\", \"from\": 2881, \"to\": 2893}, {\"ngram\": \"entry\", \"from\": 2899, \"to\": 2904}, {\"ngram\": \"the number\", \"from\": 2908, \"to\": 2918}, {\"ngram\": \"cups\", \"from\": 2922, \"to\": 2926}, {\"ngram\": \"drinking stations\", \"from\": 2937, \"to\": 2954}, {\"ngram\": \"the intricacies\", \"from\": 2958, \"to\": 2973}, {\"ngr